      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must be conducted on the same device geometry and fluid (blood analog) as the COU at Gradation 4.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used a glycerol-water blood analog at room temperature rather than porcine blood at physiological temperature. Geometric similarity was maintained but fluid rheology introduces unquantified extrapolation uncertainty. Achieved level 2."
